  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of emergency humanitarian assistance to drought-affected displaced populations in Somalia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project aims to implement a multi-sector response to the location-specific emergency needs of displaced populations and host communities in Somalia. Through camp coordination and camp management (CCCM), Health and Water, Sanitation and Hygiene Promotion (WASH) responses, IOM will strengthen existing life-saving humanitarian assistance to drought affected populations and scale up its activities in Gedo, Bay, Sanaag, and Lower Juba regions of Somalia.</narrative>
  </description>
